com.codepotato.model.effects

Class FlangerEffect

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.codepotato.model.effects.Effect
      • com.codepotato.model.effects.TimeBasedEffect
        • com.codepotato.model.effects.FlangerEffect

  • public class FlangerEffect
extends TimeBasedEffect
    Flanger is a very short delay, usually less than 15ms. Just like Chorus, the delay fluctuates up and down on a sin wave pattern. When this is done with such a short delay, it creates what some people call the "airplane" effect. It can also create a sort of robotic sound.
    Author:
    Michael Santer

      • setDepth

        public void setDepth(int percent)
        Depth represents the amount in which the delay changes. Ex: If depth is 10, the delay will fluctuate between 0ms and 10ms.
        Parameters:
        percent - Set depth as a percent from 0-100 of max Depth. Max Depth is 50.
